<div class="indented"><a id="comment-15258"></a>
  <div class="comment">
    <h3 class="title"><a href="/hotel-rooms-and-temporary-apartments-need-adapt-better-digital-nomad#comment-15258" class="active">Yikes</a></h3>    <div class="submitted">Submitted by <a href="/user/brad" title="View user profile." rel="nofollow">brad</a> on Wed, 2014-06-04 14:05.</div>
    <div class="content"><p>I have not seen that before, but it sounds very bad.   Many hotels (especially in Asia) require you to put your card key in a slot to get power in the room.  Mainly for the air conditioning, but sometimes for all the plugs, so in theory you can&#8217;t charge stuff when out of the room.</p>

<p>So I, and I am sure many others, have discovered you can usually put almost any card in there, such as a library card, and keep the power going all the time, the opposite of what they wanted.</p>
</div>
